Kano State governor, Abdullahi Ganduje has declared that the state government would drag the River State governor, Nyesom Wike, to court over the alleged demolition of Rainbow Town Central Mosque located at the Trans-Amadi area of Port Harcourt. A statement released on Saturday by Abba Anwar, Chief Press Secretary to Ganduje, described the “sad story of mosque demolition in Rivers State as shocking” promising that “necessary lawful action must be taken over the happening.” JUST IN: Action Alliance National Chairman not kidnapped, he was… New Lebanese wife of Gov Muhammed arrives Bauchi Nigerian Startup builds Anti-kidnap and Anti-theft gadget Christian leaders to members: Defend yourselves against… Zamfara gov orders immediate implementation of RUGA The statement said: “Kano State is known for peaceful coexistence between Muslims and Christians; we should therefore improve on that and remain calm and peaceful. People should live peacefully with one another.” It added that “We received this information with high degree of shock and I am assuring the general public that all necessary actions against this demolition will be taken through appropriate authorities.” Anwar added that Ganduje would institute “legal action against this demolition of the mosque and as well contest approach “appropriate authorities for redress.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
